Security Rules Backend
Prerequisites
Node.js (v16+ recommended)

MongoDB running locally or remotely (with replica set if needed)

Setup
Clone the repo and go to the backend folder

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <backend-folder>
Install dependencies

bash
Copy
Edit
npm install
Create a .env file with your database URL

ini
Copy
Edit
DATABASE_URL="mongodb://localhost:27018/rulesdb"
Generate Prisma client

bash
Copy
Edit
npx prisma generate
Build the project

bash
Copy
Edit
npm run build
Running the server
For development (with auto reload):

bash
Copy
Edit
npm run dev
For production:

bash
Copy
Edit
npm start
What it does
Automatically creates a default rule with a very high priority if none exists

Provides API to:

Get paginated rules (GET /rules?page=1)

Bulk save rules (POST /rules/bulk-save) — default rule can’t be modified

